# AhaDiff

Use AhaDiff when suggesting, reviewing, or explaining code changes that should
be learned back from the actual diff.

## Commands

- `ahadiff learn HEAD~1..HEAD` captures the latest commit.
- `ahadiff learn --staged` captures staged changes before commit.
- `ahadiff quiz <run_id>` reviews generated quiz questions.
- `ahadiff review` opens the due SRS queue.
- `ahadiff verify <run_id>` rechecks claims and score artifacts.
- `ahadiff improve <run_id>` proposes targeted improvements.
- `ahadiff serve` opens the local WebUI.

## Guidance

- Prefer AhaDiff artifacts with verified claims and file-line evidence over
  free-form summaries.
- Use `.ahadiff/runs/<run_id>/` for run artifacts such as claims, lessons,
  quizzes, scores, and provenance.
- Treat `review.sqlite` as the local review and SRS state source.
- Keep provider credentials in environment variables and do not commit private
  audit logs.
